87
00:04:03,018 --> 00:04:05,921
one of the original animated films, Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs,

88
00:04:05,921 --> 00:04:07,923
and they turned that into an attraction.

89
00:04:07,923 --> 00:04:10,525
Now in this attraction, they wanted to really immerse you in the film.

90
00:04:10,525 --> 00:04:11,946
They wanted to bring you into the movie.

91
00:04:12,507 --> 00:04:14,949
And so they created an experience where you visited

92
00:04:14,949 --> 00:04:16,870
some of the most iconic locations from the film.

93
00:04:16,870 --> 00:04:18,452
You went to the Dwarves' Diamond Mine,

94
00:04:18,452 --> 00:04:22,035
you went to the spooky dungeons, you went to the forest.

95
00:04:22,035 --> 00:04:24,097
You saw some of the most iconic characters.

96
00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:25,818
You met the dwarves, the woodland critters,

97
00:04:25,818 --> 00:04:27,259
the evil queen.

98
00:04:27,259 --> 00:04:30,062
And yet when people went on this, they were perplexed.

99
00:04:30,062 --> 00:04:34,526
You saw a lot of things from that film

100
00:04:34,526 --> 00:04:36,367
and went through all those iconic scenes,

101
00:04:36,367 --> 00:04:38,129
but you never saw Snow White.

102
00:04:39,357 --> 00:04:43,001
There was no Snow White in Snow White and Her Adventures.

103
00:04:43,001 --> 00:04:46,606
It said right on the marquee, it said her name above the door,

104
00:04:46,606 --> 00:04:48,207
and then you go on, you see all these things,

105
00:04:48,207 --> 00:04:49,990
but you don't see her.

106
00:04:49,990 --> 00:04:50,070
So.

107
00:04:50,731 --> 00:04:51,672
Where is she?

108
00:04:51,672 --> 00:04:52,472
Why wasn't she there?

109
00:04:52,472 --> 00:04:56,915
Well, our filmmakers said, when they were gathered

110
00:04:56,915 --> 00:04:59,137
around that table thinking about how do we

111
00:04:59,137 --> 00:05:01,639
put guests in the movie, they said, OK.

112
00:05:01,639 --> 00:05:06,282
This is an amazing opportunity to give our guests

113
00:05:06,282 --> 00:05:08,723
that first-person experience.

114
00:05:08,723 --> 00:05:12,986
So instead of, as you're going through,

115
00:05:12,986 --> 00:05:15,929
instead of seeing Snow White, you're going to be Snow White.

116
00:05:15,929 --> 00:05:18,110
The witch is going to offer you the apple.

117
00:05:19,262 --> 00:05:25,264
And it turned out that that was a little confusing.

118
00:05:25,264 --> 00:05:27,805
Cool idea, confusing execution.

119
00:05:27,805 --> 00:05:31,547
So part of the confusion was a first-person experience

120
00:05:31,547 --> 00:05:34,968
is just a small part of being in the movie.

121
00:05:34,968 --> 00:05:36,548
It turns out that

122
00:05:37,537 --> 00:05:40,459
Snow White's experience as you're watching her

123
00:05:40,459 --> 00:05:43,141
is a lot different than your experience

124
00:05:43,141 --> 00:05:46,623
of being in this early dark ride.

125
00:05:46,623 --> 00:05:50,266
So you are, for one thing, you are literally on rails.

126
00:05:50,266 --> 00:05:53,068
Snow White is, you're watching her make choices.

127
00:05:53,068 --> 00:05:56,310
She's deciding whether or not to go investigate

128
00:05:56,310 --> 00:05:57,671
this little sleepy cottage.

129
00:05:57,671 --> 00:05:58,712
Why is it so small?

130
00:05:58,712 --> 00:06:00,213
Who could live there?

131
00:06:00,213 --> 00:06:02,315
She's deciding whether or not to take the apple.

132
00:06:02,315 --> 00:06:04,476
You are on rails.

133
00:06:05,533 --> 00:06:07,474
Going through scene by scene, you're

134
00:06:07,474 --> 00:06:08,854
not making any of those choices.

135
00:06:08,854 --> 00:06:11,595
So your fundamental experience is

136
00:06:11,595 --> 00:06:16,096
different than that of Snow White.

137
00:06:16,096 --> 00:06:19,757
So when you're watching something on TV,

138
00:06:19,757 --> 00:06:23,538
say like a car commercial, that car commercial

139
00:06:23,538 --> 00:06:26,778
is getting you to imagine what it's like to be

140
00:06:26,778 --> 00:06:28,759
behind the wheel of the car.

141
00:06:28,759 --> 00:06:30,799
That's their whole goal is to.

142
00:06:32,213 --> 00:06:35,116
within that frame of that proscenium of that TV

143
00:06:35,116 --> 00:06:39,560
to get you to imagine yourself immersed in that car.

144
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:44,866
And as a simple message for a car commercial, great.

145
00:06:44,866 --> 00:06:46,307
But when you start to add.

146
00:06:48,383 --> 00:06:54,229
When you start to add emotions, when you start to add that narrative complexity, we don't

147
00:06:54,229 --> 00:06:59,114
get to transition directly to the experience of being that first-person perspective.

148
00:06:59,114 --> 00:07:05,581
Because what's really happening is we're ingesting all of that, what's going on on the screen,

149
00:07:05,581 --> 00:07:09,404
and we are projecting ourselves into that world.

150
00:07:09,404 --> 00:07:10,325
We're imagining.

151
00:07:12,470 --> 00:07:17,213
we're imagining what is not just what is Snow White doing,

152
00:07:17,213 --> 00:07:18,094
but what is she thinking?

153
00:07:18,094 --> 00:07:19,234
What is she feeling?

154
00:07:19,234 --> 00:07:21,095
What would it feel like if I were there?

155
00:07:21,095 --> 00:07:23,457
We're empathizing with that world,

156
00:07:23,457 --> 00:07:25,818
and we're creating it inside of our heads.

157
00:07:25,818 --> 00:07:27,980
So to put us in the world, it doesn't

158
00:07:27,980 --> 00:07:29,540
mean making us Snow White.

159
00:07:29,540 --> 00:07:34,043
It means being, it's not just the interpretation of you

160
00:07:34,043 --> 00:07:35,644
in the movie, it's.

161
00:07:36,247 --> 00:07:42,619
your experience, it's your empathy of how we get you in the movie, we make that experience

162
00:07:42,619 --> 00:07:46,566
authentic from what you view it from the inside out.

163
00:07:48,015 --> 00:07:50,596
So when we start talking about building an authentic experience

164
00:07:50,596 --> 00:07:52,077
from the inside out, one of the first things, right

